## Edge cases

- **Multilingual code-switched samples:** run Whisper with `--language auto` per
  segment; aggregate WER per detected language. Report code-switch transitions
  as a separate metric (`code-switch transition WER`).
- **Reference audio missing for similarity metric:** skip with `status: skipped,
  reason: no_reference`. Do not silently drop the metric — make the gap visible.
- **Style classifier disagrees with human panel:** when both are available,
  report both. Classifier accuracy is a proxy; human panel is ground truth.
- **Watermark extraction fails on all files:** stop the run, surface as a
  high-severity finding. Either the watermarking step is broken or the synthesis
  is destroying the watermark. Block release until resolved.
- **Sample count under 30:** run anyway, but every metric's CI will be wide.
  Tag the scorecard with `n_samples_warning: true`. Refuse to overwrite a
  production baseline from an n<30 run.
- **Dataset hash drift:** if reference text changed but task_id is the same,
  flag it — same `task_id` with different `dataset_hash` means baselines aren't
  comparable. Force the user to bump task_id (e.g., add `-v2`).
- **UTMOS unavailable:** fall back to NISQA v2; never to a hand-rolled formula.
- **Whisper hallucinates on silent or near-silent files:** filter audio with
  energy below threshold before WER computation; mark filtered files in metrics.jsonl.

---

## Dependencies

- **S9 — Eval-store schema:** this skill is the primary writer to `voice.jsonl`.
  Schema: `task_id`, `model`, `dataset_hash`, `metric`, `value`, `ci`, `run_id`, `ts`.
- **S12 — Study artifact format:** SCORECARD.md carries YAML frontmatter with
  `target`, `mode: eval`, `derived_from`.
- `/tts-design` — produces the EVAL-PLAN.md that calls this skill.
- `/voice-clone` — produces the EVAL.md that calls this skill; sets watermark
  metric automatically.
- `/prosody-control` — produces the EVAL-PERCEPT.md that calls this skill with
  style-aware metric set.
- `/eval-harness` — cross-domain orchestrator that may invoke this skill via
  `--domain speech-tts`.
- `/benchmark-models` — for cross-system comparisons; this skill provides the
  quality dimension.
- Model checkpoints (downloaded once, cached):
  - **UTMOS-22** (MOS predictor): ~100MB.
  - **NISQA v2** (MOS predictor fallback): ~80MB.
  - **ECAPA-TDNN** via SpeechBrain: ~80MB.
  - **Whisper large-v3**: ~3GB; medium: ~1.5GB.
  - **emotion2vec**: ~300MB.
  - **AudioSeal detector** (if watermark metric): ~120MB.
- Auxiliary: `pyworld` (F0), Montreal Forced Aligner (phoneme alignment),
  `faster-whisper` (CTranslate2 inference), `speechbrain` (ECAPA), `pyannote.audio`
  (alt embedding).
- Framework: PyTorch is the default runtime. JAX is not standard for these eval
  models. vLLM / SGLang do NOT apply (LLM-only stacks).

---

## Important Rules

- **Always run the full default metric set unless the user opts out per metric.**
  Skipping silently hides regressions.
- **Never overwrite a production baseline from a low-n run.** Refuse if n < 30.
- **Watermark failure is HIGH severity.** Block the run; surface immediately.
- **Mark skipped metrics explicitly.** No silent drops.
- **Dataset hash mismatch ⇒ refuse to compare** against an old baseline. Force
  task_id bump.
- **Human-MOS panels never run inline.** Emit the package and wait for results.
- **Every metric writes to S9.** The scorecard is for humans; metrics.jsonl is
  for downstream skills. Both are required outputs.
- **Cross-language WER is per-language.** Don't average across languages; that
  hides per-language failures.
